data.title: Hidden gem friendly service great food
data.text: Keep driving past the Citrus Cafe to find excellent food and service. Lots of menu options - something for everyone. Fresh veggie options. Excellent.

data.title: Friendly little locally owned cafe.
data.text: I've been here several times for lunch.  I love the Monte Cristo sandwich and the yummy quiches.  They also have great coffee and delicious homemade deserts.  Angi (the owner) is always friendly and works hard to make everyone feel welcome.  Although some may feel the prices are a little high, to me the atmosphere and charm of this old downtown building and the fact that is run by a lovely local lady makes it worth paying a bit more.  A nice place to sit a visit with friends.

data.title: My favorite breakfast/lunch place in Janesville!
data.text: I've been here a few times since moving to Janesville and each time has been fantastic.  The lady that waited on us (I think the owner?) is very outgoing and personable.  There daily coffee specials are wonderful.  My husband usually orders their lunch and accompanies his fries with the garlic dipping sauce.  The price is a little higher than your average breakfast place, however you can tell everything is homemade and the ingredients are fresh - worth the money!  The ambiance is quaint and warming.

data.title: Great Food !!
data.text:
This place is the best lunch location in Janesville !

The food although a bit pricey is great each time we have been there.

The food is made fresh everyday and is very healthy!

The tuna sandwich with potato wedges are my usual choice. In the winter the soup is delicious as well.

data.title: Cozy Atmosphere and Very Good Sandwiches
data.text: Very nice cafe with very good soups, sandwiches and deserts.  It appears that everything is made daily or on demand.  My favorite sandwich is their Monte Cristo.  If you are looking for a nice lunch in downtown Janesville this is an excellent choice.

data.title: Surprisingly good!
data.text: The food here is excellent and homemade, but the service can be hit or miss. The brunch after the farmer's market is really nice, quick and inexpensive. The breakfast sandwiches are my favorite. They have delicious desserts, too!
